race.description: Lesley Ann Leonard Memorial Ht 3 H
race.comment: CLUB MIAMI (1) struggled in tougher grade last start after drifting back at Wentworth Park, but prior to that won by 2.75 lengths at Temora (25.98) beating Allergy Free in a Grade 5 on July 2. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Has winning claims on his best figures. ADA TARO (2) has not raced since scoring (25.30) over 388m at Gosford 12 weeks ago. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. ELSA ABOVE (6) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 431m at Gunnedah, taking a Grade 5 in a swift 24.89. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. SCOTCH ALL ROUND (7) is in the mix after placing last time out.
